l.jpg", "displayName": "Right Angle News Network", "username": "Rightanglenews"}, "content": "BREAKING - A CBS reporter in Austin, Texas, is being massively praised after refusing to follow a text message from his superior telling him not to focus on a massive crowd praising President Trump\u2019s actions in Iran.\n\n\u201cThey don\u2019t want us to focus on this.\u201d\n\n\u201cWell, I am.\u201d", "parentTweet": false, "likes": 89830}}, "post_flair_text": "", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "text", "uuid": "1ASG4rZLoG", "is_twitter": false, "is_admin": false, "score": 196, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "", "id": 8462488, "raw_content": "This nation was in the midst of the worst presidency, pre eggplant, in history. Gas shortages when there never needed to have been were prevalent. Inflation, unemployment, and interest were out of control. Under the peanut farmer, the misery index (inflation + unemployment) reached 21%. That broke down as 7.5% unemployment and 13.5% inflation. On Dec 20, 1980 (from memory) the prime lending rate exceeded 20%.\n\nIn November of 79, radical revolutionaries held our entire nation in submission as it took 66 American hostages and the feckless admin of Jimma was powerless. Again prior to eggplant, Jimma was the weakest president of the past 100 years. Although, he was perhaps not nearly as corrupt as the more recent iterations of pathetic and catastrophic presidencies.\n\nA song by Tony Orlando and Dawn (written about 4 years prior) became a rallying cry for America during the hostage crisis which played out on wooden or furniture console cathode ray tubes barely 20\" diagonal, but in color. America was at a low point.\n\nThose who remember this time period even if noninterventionist now, are likely to feel differently that those who do not about the current strikes on Iran.\n\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Z8fhciUojQ0", "author": "dataonly", "created": 1772546534952, "profile_picture": "", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "DebbieinDallas", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "", "removal_source": "", "link": "", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "Most Anyone Who was 10 Yrs or Older in 1979 Will Feel Differently than Those Who Never Lived It", "last_comment_created": 1772567907259, "content": "<p>This nation was in the midst of the worst presidency, pre eggplant, in history. Gas shortages when there never needed to have been were prevalent. Inflation, unemployment, and interest were out of control. Under the peanut farmer, the misery index (inflation + unemployment) reached 21%. That broke down as 7.5% unemployment and 13.5% inflation. On Dec 20, 1980 (from memory) the prime lending rate exceeded 20%.</p>\n<p>In November of 79, radical revolutionaries held our entire nation in submission as it took 66 American hostages and the feckless admin of Jimma was powerless. Again prior to eggplant, Jimma was the weakest president of the past 100 years. Although, he was perhaps not nearly as corrupt as the more recent iterations of pathetic and catastrophic presidencies.</p>\n<p>A song by Tony Orlando and Dawn (written about 4 years prior) became a rallying cry for America during the hostage crisis which played out on wooden or furniture console cathode ray tubes barely 20&quot; diagonal, but in color. America was at a low point.</p>\n<p>Those who remember this time period even if noninterventionist now, are likely to feel differently that those who do not about the current strikes on Iran.</p>\n<p><a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Z8fhciUojQ0\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Z8fhciUojQ0</a></p>\n", "score_down": 4, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_